## 🧠 2. Tier 1: The Defensive Brain (Wazuh Manager)

The Wazuh Manager handles the collection, indexing, and alerting of all system telemetry.

### Provisioning the VM / LXC

* **Base OS:** Ubuntu 22.04 LTS or Debian 12 (64-bit)
* **Compute Allocation:** 2–4 vCPUs, 4–8 GB RAM, 50 GB+ Storage (SSD preferred for indexing logs).
* **Network Assignment:** Attach to the isolated bridge (`vmbr1`) and assign a static IP: `192.168.99.5/24`.

### Installation Steps

The most efficient deployment method for a standalone lab is using the automated Wazuh single-node installation script. Run the following command inside your clean Ubuntu/Debian instance:

```bash
curl -sO https://packages.wazuh.com/4.x/wazuh-install.sh && sudo bash wazuh-install.sh -a

```

Once completed, the terminal will print a secure password for the admin account. Navigate to `[https://192.168.99.5](https://192.168.99.5)` in a browser within your lab network to log into the dashboard.

